ORSF predictions

Source: R/orsf_predict.R
predict.aorsf.Rd

ORSF predictions

# S3 method for aorsf
predict(object, new_data, times, risk = TRUE, ...)

Arguments

object

(aorsf) an oblique random survival forest (ORSF; see orsf).

new_data

(data.frame) data to compute predictions for. Must have the same columns with equivalent types as the data used to train object. Also, factors in new_data must not have levels that were not in the data used to train object. Last, missing data are not supported.

times

(double) a single time or a vector of times for oblique RSF predictions. All times values must not exceed the maximum follow-up time in the oblique RSF's training data. Also, times must be entered in ascending order.

risk

(logical) if TRUE, predicted risk is returned. If FALSE, predicted survival (i.e., 1-risk) is returned.

...

not used.

Value

a matrix of predictions. Column j of the matrix corresponds to value j in times. Row i of the matrix corresponds to row iin new_data.

Examples


train <- seq(1, nrow(pbc_orsf), by = 2)
test <- seq(2, nrow(pbc_orsf), by = 2)

fit <- orsf(pbc_orsf[train, ], Surv(time, status) ~ . - id)

preds <- predict(fit,
                 new_data = pbc_orsf[test, ],
                 times = c(500, 1500, 2500))

head(preds)
